, the dipole is saturated by a non-local interaction involving the\nmost energetic scale of the magnetic energy spectrum, which points out the\nimportance of the magnetic Prandtl number for large-scale dynamos.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Jan 2013 17:37:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-11-18"}
